==English==
===Etymology===
named for [[w:Werner Heisenberg|Werner Heisenberg]], its discoverer
===Noun phrase===
{{wikipediapar|uncertainty principle}}
'''[[Heisenberg]] [[uncertainty]] [[principle]]'''
#{{physics}} in [[quantum mechanics]], the principle that there is an [[absolute]] [[limit]] on the [[combined]] [[accuracy]] of certain [[pair]]s of [[simultaneous]], [[related]] [[measurement]]s, especially that of the [[position]] and [[momentum]] of a [[particle]]

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[Heisenbergin epätarkkuusperiaate]]

===Synonyms===
*[[uncertainty principle]]
*[[indeterminacy principle]]
